5.3.2021   
EN
Official Journal of the European Union
CI 76/9
COVID – 19 outbreak

         

            
(Regulation (EU) 2021/267 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 February 2021 laying down specific and temporary measures in view of the persistence of the COVID-19 crisis concerning the renewal or extension of certain certificates, licences and authorisations, the postponement of certain periodic checks and periodic training in certain areas of transport legislation and the extension of certain periods referred to in Regulation (EU) 2020/698
 
1
)

      
(2021/C 76 I/05)

         
The Netherlands

      

         
Date of the Information to the Commission
: 22.2.2021

         
The Netherlands
 has decided, in conformity with the relevant provisions of Regulation (EU) 2021/267 of the European Parliament and of the Council 
that it shall not apply the following provisions:

      
—
Article 4(1) concerning the regular inspections of tachographs in road transport under Regulation (EU) No 165/2014 
2
;
—
Article 4(2) concerning the renewal of driver cards under Regulation (EU) No 165/2014;
—
Article 4(3) concerning the replacement of driver cards under Regulation (EU) No 165/2014;
—
Article 5(1) concerning the time limits for the periodic roadworthiness tests for motor vehicles and their trailers under Directive 2014/45/EU 
3
;
—
Article 5(2) concerning the validity of roadworthiness certificates under Directive 2014/45/EU;
—
Article 7(1) concerning the validity of the Community licence for road haulage under Regulation (EC) No 1072/2009 
4
;
—
Article 7(2) concerning the validity of the driver attestation under Regulation (EC) No 1072/2009;
—
Article 8(1) concerning the validity of the Community licence for passenger transport under Regulation (EC) No 1073/2009 
5
;
—
Article 9(1) concerning the time limits for renewal of single safety certificates under Directive (EU) 2016/798 
6
;
—
Article 9(2) concerning the validity of safety authorisations under Directive (EU) 2016/798;
—
Article 10(1) concerning the time limits for renewal of safety certificates under Directive 2004/49/EC 
7
;
—
Article 10(2) concerning the time limits for renewal of safety authorisations under Directive (EU) 2004/49/EC;
—
Article 12(2) concerning the validity of temporary licences under Directive 2012/34/EU 
8
;
—
Article 14(1) concerning the time limits for undergoing medical examinations under Directive 96/50/EC 
9
;
—
Article 15(1) concerning the validity of Union inland navigation certificates under Directive (EU) 2016/1629 
10
;
—
Article 15(2) concerning the validity of documents falling within the scope of Directive (EU) 2016/1629 and issued under Directive 2006/87/EC 
11
;

         
